decks.notes: This Esper Control deck focuses on manipulating the game state and disrupting the opponent's strategies. The key concept revolves around using a combination of powerful spells and artifacts to control the game and create advantage. It utilizes cards like Yawgmoth's Will and Tinker to access and play key cards from the graveyard. It also combines efficient control spells like Force of Will and Swords to Plowshares with card draw and library manipulation effects like Brainstorm and Sensei's Divining Top. The deck is designed to outlast and outmaneuver the opponent, ultimately leading to victory.

This deck aims to control the game by utilizing cards like Force of Will and Paradoxical Outcome to manipulate the battlefield. The key strategy involves using Oath of Druids to cheat powerful creatures like Atraxa, Grand Unifier into play quickly. The deck also includes various artifact and mana ramp cards to generate resources and outpace opponents. With cards like Tinker and Bolas's Citadel, the deck can create explosive plays and overwhelming advantages. Overall, the deck focuses on disrupting opponents while establishing a strong board presence and ultimately dominating the game.

The main concept of this deck is to aggressively use Bazaar of Baghdad to fuel graveyard cards like Vengevine and Hollow One, while also disrupting opponents with Wasteland and Force of Will. The deck aims to quickly overwhelm opponents with powerful creatures and disruptive spells, using cards like Noxious Revival and Force of Vigor to maintain advantage. The inclusion of Squee, Goblin Nabob and Master of Death allows for recurring threats, while Poxwalkers and Chalice of the Void provide additional disruption. Overall, the deck is focused on fast, aggressive gameplay and disrupting opponents' strategies.
